<subSubSection id="C3496520B14FC069FF62FCDD400DC0DD" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB14FC069FF62FCDD4216C45E" blockId="2.[151,455,819,881]" box="[151,267,855,881]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
(
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FF6AFCDD421FC45E" box="[159,258,855,881]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Figs 1–9</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB14FC069FF62FC15420EC29D" blockId="2.[151,1437,927,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B14FC069FF62FC15426EC496" box="[151,371,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body uniformly brown (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FD65FC1541CDC496" box="[656,720,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); antennal segments I–II brown, III yellow, IV pale at distal half and brown on remaining part, V–IX brown (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FD72FC4941D1C4F2" box="[647,716,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Fore wing with a brownish base and long transverse dark band in the middle, base and apex pale, clavus brown; all legs dark brown with tibiae and tarsi pale. Head longer than wider, arched at cheeks, with close transverse striae; postocular setae in 2 rows but irregularly arranged medially and laterally (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FEC5FBA54269C365" box="[304,372,1071,1098]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); mouth cone pointed and extending between fore coxae, maxillary palp segment II subdivided. Antennal segments III–IV with sensorium vermicular and curving around apex, with internal markings, sensoria 0.7 and 0.8 times as long as length of segments (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FD7AFBFD41CEC3BE" box="[655,723,1143,1169]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Pronotum as long as wide, densely sculptured with transverse striae, with about 50 discal setae and 3 pairs of posteromarginal setae, S1 stouter. Mesonotum tightly sculptured with densely transverse striae, internal markings near posterior area; lateral and posteromedian setae short and stout; anteromedian CPS absent (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FDF8FB69414EC3D2" box="[525,595,1251,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Metascutum anteromedian area with transverse dense sculpture lines and posteromedian short reticulations, with small wrinkles between sculpture lines, median pair of setae near posterior margin; CPS absent (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FE72FAA142D3C26A" box="[391,462,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergite I with 2 transverse lines on anterior part, II-VIII smooth medially (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FF55FAC543F8C245" box="[160,229,1359,1386]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Sternites II–VII each with 3, 4, 4, 4, 5(rarely 4), 5 pairs of posteromarginal setae, submarginal on VII, 2 pairs of accessory setae between S1 and S2; sternites III–VII with 1–5 pairs of discal setae (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FB48FAF9461EC2A1" box="[1213,1283,1395,1422]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), VIII with 1 discal seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB14FC069FF32FA31469FC2D6" blockId="2.[151,1437,927,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B14FC069FF32FA31426CC2FA" bold="true" box="[199,369,1467,1493]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Measurements</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54E88809B14FC069FE8BFA3142C2C2FA" box="[382,479,1467,1493]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
in microns). Body length 1882; head length 194, width 180. (Pronotum length 185, width 188). Fore wing length 707, median width 109. Antennal segments I–IX length: 36, 44, 116, 106, 59, 49, 39, 14, 16.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB14FC069FF32F9894298C181" blockId="2.[151,1437,927,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B14FC069FF32F9894295C132" box="[199,392,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Male macroptera</emphasis>
. Similar to but smaller and paler than female(
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FC8AF98940A3C132" box="[895,958,1539,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); antennal segment II pale at apex, segment III pale at base; fore wings weakly narrowed and long (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FD08F9AD405CC16E" box="[765,833,1575,1601]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palps 3-segmented, segment II undivided. Abdominal tergite I with two longitudinal ridges, IX without curved claspers, S1 setae slightly longer than S2 (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB14FC069FA9AF9C143BAC1A6" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1435,179,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Aduncothrips albus sp.n. (1) Body of female; (2) Body of male; (3) Tergites VII-X of male; (4) Meso and metanotum; (5) Head and pronotum; (6) Sternites III-VII of female; (7) Tergites VIII-X of female; (8) Forewing of male; (9) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Sternites II–VII with 3 pairs of posteromarginal setae, VIII with 4 pairs posteromarginal setae, V–VIII each with 1 pair of discal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB14FC069FF32F93D43F9C036" blockId="2.[151,1437,927,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B14FC069FF32F93D426BC1FE" bold="true" box="[199,374,1719,1745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Measurements</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54E88809B14FC069FE73F93D42F5C1FE" box="[390,488,1719,1745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">paratype</typeStatus>
in microns). Body length 1324; head length 178, width 162. (Pronotum length 155, width 185). Fore wing length 670, median width 75. Antennal segments I–IX length: 29, 45, 107, 89, 55, 44, 38, 16, 10.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB14FC069FF32F8A9400DC0DD" blockId="2.[151,1437,927,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B14FC069FF32F8A942AAC012" bold="true" box="[199,439,1827,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Specimens studied.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B3B3CF6B14FC069FE3FF8A94018C04D" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3785191306" collectedFrom="on grass" collectingDate="2014-07-27" collectorName="Zhang Hongrui" country="China" county="Heqing County" latitude="26.473208" location="Heqing County" longitude="100.306946" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-female="1" stateProvince="YUNNAN Province" typeStatus="holotype">
