<subSubSection id="C3496520B149C06FFF32FF1C408BC79F" box="[199,918,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB149C06FFF32FF1C408BC79F" blockId="4.[151,1436,150,321]" box="[199,918,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B149C06FFF32FF1C4253C79F" bold="true" box="[199,334,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the pale tibiae and tarsi.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3496520B149C06FFF32FF30407CC66F" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB149C06FFF32FF30407CC66F" blockId="4.[151,1436,150,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B149C06FFF32FF304252C7FB" bold="true" box="[199,335,186,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Comments.</emphasis>
This new species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D28B149C06FFCF9FF314064C7FB" authorityName="Li &amp; Elie &amp; Liu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Elie &amp; Liu &amp; Zhang" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[780,889,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Aeolothripidae" genus="Aduncothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B149C06FFCF9FF314064C7FB" box="[780,889,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the key above. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D28B149C06FFB3FFF31463BC7FB" authorityName="Li &amp; Elie &amp; Liu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1226,1318,186,213]" class="Insecta" family="Aeolothripidae" genus="Aduncothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albus">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B149C06FFB3FFF31463BC7FB" box="[1226,1318,186,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. albus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has all the tibiae and tarsi sharply paler than the brown femora, and the very long extension of the filamentous sensorium on segment III does not extend to the base. The species 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D28B149C06FFD07FE89406BC633" authorityName="Ramakrishna &amp; Margabandhu, 1931:" authorityYear="1029" box="[754,886,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Aeolothripidae" genus="Erythrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B149C06FFD07FE89406BC633" box="[754,886,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has the tibiae and tarsi yellow, but has fore wings with a longitudinal dark band along the posterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
